Cell C has confirmed it will increase prices inline with the Treasury’s hike of VAT from 14% to 15% on 1 April. Subscribers to Cell C’s Black video streaming service received the following message on the matter: Dear Valued Client, as announced, the VAT rate will increase to 15% on 1 April 2018. Our services are subject to VAT increase. More information will be communicated in due course. Thank you. Team black Cell C confirmed it has started notifying clients that it will adjust its pricing as a result of the VAT increase. “More information will be communicated to customers in due course,” said Cell C.